# KeepnetLabs Vue 2 Frontend Development Rules

## Project Overview
This project is built with Vue 2.7.8, Vuetify 2.6.9, and follows enterprise-grade development practices. As a Senior Frontend Developer working on this project, you are expected to:

- Write clean, maintainable, and scalable code
- Follow Vue 2 Options API patterns
- Implement proper state management with Vuex
- Use Vuetify components effectively
- Ensure high performance and accessibility
- Maintain code quality and consistency
- Follow security best practices
- Document your code properly

## Development Environment
- Vue 2.7.8
- Vuetify 2.6.9
- Vuex 3.4.0
- Vue Router 3.3.4
- Axios 0.27.2
- ESLint & Prettier for code quality
- Jest for testing

## Senior Frontend Developer Coding Guidelines

### Code Writing Style
- Always write code as if the next developer is a psychopath who knows where you live
- Write code that is easy to delete, not easy to extend
- If you can't explain it to a six-year-old, you don't understand it yourself
- Code is like humor. When you have to explain it, it's bad
- Always code as if the guy who ends up maintaining your code will be a violent psychopath who knows where you live
- The best code is no code at all
- The only way to go fast is to go well
- Clean code always looks like it was written by someone who cares

